        conduct allreduce operation on shared chunks in the given range. Note: please use the same ranges in all the places.
        Type Parameters:
        U - the type of the extracted data
        Parameters:
        ranges - the list of ranges in which chunks are applied to the operation.
        pack - the function that receives an element and extracts data that will be transferred to other places and be reduced by the unpack operation.
        unpack - the function that receives a local element and the transferred data from each place and conducts reduction operation to the local element.

      • share

        public void share(List<LongRange> ranges,
                  handist.collections.dist.CollectiveRelocator.Allgather mm)
        conduct broadcast operation on chunks that are not shared with other places yet. The user must call each of the share methods of a cachable chunked list in all the place belonging to the place group. This method should not be called simultaneously with other collective methods. The caller place is treated as the owner even if the chunks become shared. Note 1: if you want to share all the local chunks, please call share(). Note 2: if you want to specify multiple ranges, please use share(List<LongRange>). Note 3: if you don't want to share any local chunks from the called place, please specify an empty range or an empty list of ranges. Note 3: if you want to conduct relocate process of multiple cachable chunked lists using the same ObjectOutput(Stream), please prepare an instance of CollectiveRelocator.Allgather first and call the relocation methods of the cachable chunked lists in the same order specifying the collective relocator as a parameter, and finally call the execute method of the relocator.
        Parameters:
        ranges - The library scans the ranges and exports (the parts of) the local chunks in the ranges.
        mm - You can relocate multiple cachable chunked lists using the same collective relocator, specified with mm.

        public Object writeReplace()
                    throws ObjectStreamException
        Description copied from interface: DistributedCollection
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place

        Specified by:

        Overrides:

        Returns:

        Throws:
        ObjectStreamException - if such an exception is thrown during the process
